Review:
Gaasperplas is een openbare park waar de groten onder de raggea artisten als Morgan Heritage, Alborosie,Tarrus Riley, third world, Etana, Ziggy Marley, kimani Marley en nog vele anderen optreden.
In de zomer maanden is het elk jaar, een verrassing welke artiesten, door de organisatie van reggae lake festival, naar binnen gehaald worden. Klantvriendelijk. Gedeeltelijk rolstoelvriendelijk met begeleiding. Het is zeer druk.  Lange wachtrijen voor kaarten, gaat toch vlot, openbare toiletten aanwezig. Honden aan de lijn. Bussen 41, 44, eind halte metro 53. gaasperplas. Van uit Station Duivendrecht overstappen op de metro 54 richtig CS en overstappen aan de van der Made weg op de metro 53, richting gaasperplas eindhalte voor dit grote reggae festival twee dagen lang.

Gaasperplas is a public park where the greats among the raggea artists like Morgan Heritage, Alborosie,Tarrus Riley, third world, Etana, Ziggy Marley, kimani Marley and many others perform.
In the summer months, every year, it is a surprise which artists, are brought in by the organization of reggae lake festival. Customer Friendly. Partially wheelchair friendly with guidance. It is very busy.  Long queues for tickets, still goes smoothly, public restrooms available. Dogs on leash. Buses 41, 44, end stop metro 53. gaasperplas. From station Duivendrecht change to metro 54 direction CS and change at van der Made road to metro 53, direction gaasperplas final stop for this big reggae festival two days long.

There was a tray of beer and lemonade waiting for a waitress and she only came to get the tray after 10 minutes. There was pleasant chatter behind the bar and everyone looked at us and saw us not drinking anything.
Of course I know that on a hot day there isn't really a shot in the arm but I have worked in the hospitality industry and know that it can be veeeeeeeeeery more professional!!! It was a disappointment.

Review:
A lake in which people can swim. Very nice in the summer! Near the roundabout between the streets Noordzijde and Oostoever there is a pier (wood and stone) where you can seat and soak your feet, sunbathe or jump into the lake (there are also stairs to go in the water). Dogs allowed (it's a public place), haven't seen dogs swimming, though; I guess because there is no easy way for them to go out of the water (there's no shore it's a pier). Only some occasional seaweed and very little waste in the water. Depending on the time there might not be any shadows to cover yourself from the sun! There is a point of drinking water near the roundabout!
You can also swim  in this lake or lie at Sloterpark.

Review: Jeugdland ligt op een klein schiereiland aan de rand van het Flevopark. Om er te komen moet u eerst langs tennisvereniging Tie-breakers. Voor de ingang van de tennisvereniging en Jeugdland zijn ongeveer 10 parkeerplekken, waarvoor op bepaalde tijden moet worden betaald. Jeugdland bestaat uit een kinderboerderij, een clubhuis, een skelterlab, een jeugdlab, een speeltuin voor kleinere kinderen en plek waar houten hutten gemaakt worden. Het terrein is groot. In het clubhuis is naschoolse opvang en ruimte die u kunt afhuren voor bijvoorbeeld een kinderfeestje. Ook kunt u hier o.a. koffie, thee en gebak bestellen. Het gebak is erg lekker. Buiten is er een terras van o.a. picknickbanken. Dieren in de kinderboerderij zijn o.a. geiten, een ezel, pauwen en knaagdieren.
Translated_Review: Youth Land is located on a small peninsula at the edge of Flevopark. To get there, you must first pass tennis club Tie-breakers. There are about 10 parking spots in front of the entrance to the tennis club and Jeugdland, which require payment at certain times. Jeugdland consists of a petting zoo, a clubhouse, a go-kart lab, a youth lab, a playground for smaller children and place where wooden huts are made. The grounds are large. In the clubhouse is after-school care and space that you can rent for a children's party, for example. You can also order coffee, tea and pastries here, among other things. The pastries are very tasty. Outside there is a terrace of picnic benches, among other things. Animals in the petting zoo include goats, a donkey, peacocks and rodents.

Review:
Het Erasmuspark is een fijn park. Niet heel groot. Er wordt veel in gesport door groepjes  volwassenen en kinderen. En er zijn ook trainingsapparaten aanwezig.

In het park bevindt zich een bloementuin met lange banken waar je op kan zitten. Verderop zit een speeltuin met grote zandbak, glijbaan, huisje. Leuk voor de kleintjes. Aansluitend zit het 'Terrasmus' waar je een hapje kunt eten (broodje, tosti) of wat kunt drinken. Zowel binnen als buiten kun je zitten. Ook kun je je koffie meenemen naar de speeltuin (handig!). Achter het eettentje zitten wc's waar je gebruik van kan maken.

Park is hondvriendelijk. Volgens mij mag je de hond in een groot gedeelte van het park uitlaten.

In de zomer kun je een plons nemen in de gracht, naast het park. Ideaal.
Translated_Review:
Erasmus Park is a fine park. Not very big. A lot of sports are played in it by groups of adults and children. And there are exercise machines there as well.

In the park there is a flower garden with long benches you can sit on. Further on is a playground with large sandbox, slide, house. Fun for the little ones. Adjacent is the 'Terrasmus' where you can have a snack (sandwich, toasted sandwich) or a drink. Both inside and outside you can sit. You can also take your coffee to the playground (handy!). Behind the eatery are toilets you can use.

Park is dog friendly. I think you can walk your dog in a large part of the park.

In the summer you can take a splash in the moat, next to the park. Ideal.

Review:
Bijzonder stukje Amsterdam. Sfeervol en alternatief aan het water in Noord. Opgetuigd uit gebruikte materialen en 2e hands zitmeubilair. Leuke sfeer. Bediening prima.

De drankenkaart kan echt beter idd. Prima om geen frisdrank te serveren, maar zorg dan voor een uitgebreider aanbod in verse sapjes en lekker speciaalbier (la Chouffe, Texels..). Jullie hebben alleen jus uit verpakking en dat vind ik weer helemaal krom. Uiteindelijk maar blond biertje besteld en dan blijkt het Gulpener te zijn. Het enige bier dat ik echt niet lust.

-------

Beste eigenaar, in reactie op je reactie. Je reageert altijd een beetje stekelig op feedback helaas. Ik geef je 4-sterren en heb ook gemeld dat je gelegenheid enorme potentie heeft. Het is een toffe plek, met gave aankleding en atmosfeer. Kennelijk kun je niet zo heel goed met feedback omgaan. Het specifieke verhaal hieronder...

Toen ik naar iets als cassis vroeg op het terras, werd mij gemeld dat jullie geen frisdrank hebben! Dat ten eerste. Toen ik vroeg naar bier, kreeg ik een vage abstract van jullie kennelijk geweldige aanbod. Er was een blond biertje dus dacht, ik neem dat maar.

Verder zitten de helft van je klanten te werken  en binnen hoor je (best wel hard maar oke), 70's muziek in de zaak en hiphop uit de keuken, door elkaar. Mogen we daar iets van vinden?

Ik zou zeggen, maak iets duidelijkere keuzes in wat je wilt zijn, zorg dat je personeel het aanbod goed kent of maak een leuke drankenkaart en neem feedback iets minder stekelig in ontvangst. Dan kun je mij in de toekomst vaak terugzien, als enigszins goedbedoeld kritische gasten tenminste welkom zijn.
Translated_Review:
Special piece of Amsterdam. Atmospheric and alternative by the water in North. Rigged out of used materials and 2nd hand seating. Nice atmosphere. Service fine.

Beverage menu could really be better idd. Fine not to serve soft drinks, but make sure you have a wider range of fresh juices and good special beer (la Chouffe, Texels...). You only have gravy from packaging and I find that totally crooked again. In the end I ordered a blond beer and it turned out to be Gulpener. The only beer I really don't like.

-------

Dear owner, in response to your comment. You always react a bit prickly to feedback unfortunately. I give you 4 stars and also reported that your opportunity has huge potential. It's a cool place, with cool decor and atmosphere. Apparently you can't handle feedback very well. The specific story below...

When I asked for something like cassis on the terrace, I was informed that you don't have soda! That first of all. When I asked about beer, I was given a vague abstract of your apparently great offerings. There was a blonde beer so thought I'd take that.

Furthermore, half of your customers are sitting down to work and inside you hear (pretty loud but okay), 70's music in the case and hip-hop from the kitchen, mixed together. Are we allowed to think anything about that?

I would say, make a little clearer choices in what you want to be, make sure your staff knows the offerings well or make a nice drink menu and take feedback a little less prickly. Then you can see me back often in the future, at least when somewhat well-meaning critical guests are welcome.
Cleaned_Review: special piece of amsterdam. atmospheric and alternative by the water in north. rigged out of used materials and 2nd hand seating. nice atmosphere. service fine. beverage menu could really be better idd. fine not to serve soft drinks, but make sure you have a wider range of fresh juices and good special beer (la chouffe, texels...). you only have gravy from packaging and i find that totally crooked again. in the end i ordered a blond beer and it turned out to be gulpener. the only beer i really don't like. ------- dear owner, in response to your comment. you always react a bit prickly to feedback unfortunately. i give you 4 stars and also reported that your opportunity has huge potential. it's a cool place, with cool decor and atmosphere. apparently you can't handle feedback very well. the specific story below... when i asked for something like cassis on the terrace, i was informed that you don't have soda! that first of all. when i asked about beer, i was given a vague abstract of your apparently great offerings. there was a blonde beer so thought i'd take that. furthermore, half of your customers are sitting down to work and inside you hear (pretty loud but okay), 70's music in the case and hip-hop from the kitchen, mixed together. are we allowed to think anything about that? i would say, make a little clearer choices in what you want to be, make sure your staff knows the offerings well or make a nice drink menu and take feedback a little less prickly. then you can see me back often in the future, at least when somewhat well-meaning critical guests are welcome.

dinner-1 person- september 3. 2022 saturday very enchanting environment, fine cooking, creative and well designed vegan menu, but very disappointed on service was ordered -4€ bread with olive oil, starter -18€ ravioli in seaweed butter,main dish -2€ glass of sparkling water -6,5€ glass of ipa from tap -33€ in total for 1 person with tips it up looking forward to enjoying the whole sustainable and local economy oriented dining experience, i found the service and attitude offered by the staff somewhat disappointing. personally greeted and accompanied to my seats upon arrival, the beginning was very pleasant. but the service only went downhill after that. ordering before i was even reaching my chair, my waiter offered me bread and olive oil, without explaining that this would charge 4€ on the menu. being used to house-served free bread and olive oil in most restaurants in germany, austria, france and italy, just to name a few countries in europe, i didn’t hesitate and said yes please. i only realized my order without being aware of it after i had time to actually look at the menu.the bread came however quite quickly so i decided to overlook this quite frankly trickery-move from my waiter and went further with main dish ordering. ordering he did a good job in taking the actual orders, but didn’t notice that i barely touched the bread. the fact was i didn’t like the powdered dip and wanted some salt with my olive oil instead. but since no one asked once how i liked it, i was a bit offended so i barely touch it and asked for it to be packed in a paper bag. yet no one even bothers to think about or care about why. later i was also fighting with my main dish as i suddenly felt not so well, of course i think it’s not their fault that i felt sick, but even though i shared with my waiter when he came to take my plate away, that i wasn’t feeling so great, he didn’t respond at all and just left with my leftover. the sustainable way would be asking if there’s anything wrong with it or if i would like to have it packed it up with my bread. concept & service quality yes it was saturday night, and i could see they are fully booked and very busy. but for a business that openly talks about beliefs in quality dining, sustainability and the awareness of the damages food industries bring to our planet, being busy shouldn’t become an issue. the service staff pushed customers to order and didn‘t really bother with the perception of their food. as a result there was food waste and i am sure this happens to other customers too. hopefully only when they are super busy. the concept and action doesn’t really add up.

Review:
Om hier een biertje te drinken MOET je je gegevens verstrekken aan jamezz, je email adres, telefoonnummer, naam en bankgegevens. Je kan niet cash noch gewoon met je pinpas bestellen. Ik vindt dit echt superbelachelijk voor een biertje, dat je al deze gegevens moet verstrekken, erg kwalijk. Net even de privacy verklaring gelezen van jamezz

Jamezz B.V. deelt jouw persoonsgegevens met verschillende derden als dit noodzakelijk is voor het
uitvoeren van de overeenkomst en om te voldoen aan een eventuele wettelijke verplichting

- Verzenden van onze nieuwsbrief en/of reclamefolder
- Je te kunnen bellen of e-mailen indien dit nodig is om onze dienstverlening uit te kunnen voeren
- Je te informeren over wijzigingen van onze diensten en producten

Je betaald dus voor je biertje en ze nemen er bovenop nog winst op je persoonsgegevens.
Ik ga er niet meer komen, de flair is er wel af met zo een invasief beleid.
Translated_Review:
To have a beer here you MUST provide your details to jamezz, your email address, phone number, name and bank details. You cannot order cash nor just with your debit card. I find this really super ridiculous for a beer, that you have to provide all this data, very bad. Just read the privacy statement of jamezz

Jamezz B.V. shares your personal data with various third parties if this is necessary for the
execution of the agreement and to comply with any legal obligation

- Sending our newsletter and/or advertising folder
- Calling or e-mailing you if this is necessary to carry out our services
- Inform you about changes in our services and products

So you pay for your beer and they take profit on your personal data on top of it.
I won't go there anymore, the flair is gone with such an invasive policy.

Review: The place has a fantastic ambiance. However the food was a bit disappointing and being an expensive restaurant made it even more disappinting.  The dishes were very interesting with unusual great ideas, some were really tasty, like ravioli with poppy seed, dill and hazelnut topping. But many of the flavors were really unbalanced. That ravioli had way too much balsamic vinegar and the filling was potato which in my opinion not great with pasta. And it was 17 euros. The pom pom dish (a deep fried musroom) could have been great bc of the unusual type of mushroom used, but it was way too oily. It was served with red cabbage which tasted more of cloves than cabbage. The sauce thoguh was really well made. And I also liked the chocolat pasta. One more thing: we got a hot apple juice with 30% alcohol which was merely hot and didnt taste like alcohol at all. Oh btw there were some issues with the ordering and some of our orders didnt get through although we payed.

Review:
Amazing Ambiance, that's a green house where we were seated with a sufficiently warming heater, there were blankets as well. :)
The place could've been in Spain or someother part of the world. I felt nostalgic for places I've not been to. :) If ever vegan restaurant was made to be this hip, we'd have less people eating meat I think. There are more than few example I can give that other restaurant can take from books of 'Café de Ceuvel'.

Example 1 : gracious selection of food, won't fall away from sensory pleasures you are used to. While still eating vegan food. Crispy pom pom blanc. Chocolate pasta.

Example 2 : Cocktail selection was magnificent, it was just intriguing to just try all of them. Apple sauce drink was amazing !

So why I still gave one star is because half of (Jemezz app) our order didn't make it to their system. Once they checked our bank transaction and accepted the order.
Next time I just gave up and threw the shrodingers cat philosophy for my drink . And the cat was indeed not in the box. :(

Vegan ervaring is top en knap wat ze met goede, verse groenten op tafel weten te zetten. De variatie tussen warm en koud zou wat beter mogen, een koude curry bloemkool heeft simpelweg minder smaak dan warm.

Een mooi terras met mooie tent als overkapping. Heerlijk zitten tijdens de Nederlandse 'zomer'.  Fijne sfeer, prima prijs-kwaliteit (duurzaam is gewoonweg duurder, wel je portemonnee waard  voor de planeet) en leuke bediening. In het begin duurde het even voordat we konden bestellen en was de bediening nergens te vinden. Het was ook druk en even later leken er meer medewerkers op de vloer te staan en konden we goed door met rondjes. Hier kom ik zeker nog eens terug!
Translated_Review:
Vegan experience is top notch and clever what they manage to put on the table with good, fresh vegetables. The variation between hot and cold could be a bit better, a cold curry cauliflower simply has less flavor than hot.

A nice terrace with a nice tent as cover. Lovely sitting during the Dutch 'summer'.  Nice atmosphere, great value for money (sustainable is simply more expensive, well worth your wallet for the planet) and nice service. In the beginning it took a while before we could order and the service was nowhere to be found. It was also busy and a little later there seemed to be more staff on the floor and we were able to get through with rounds well. This is definitely where I will come back!

Review:
If you want to escape the tourist mass of the city center of Amsterdam, this is the place you should go to (and don’t forget your towel)!

Located in Amsterdam Noord, this amazing place offers a Café/restaurant, good music and a little lake or canal (I’m not quite sure) right next to De Ceuvel where you can dip in for a little swim!

The atmosphere is quite relaxed and therefore it is a good place to enjoy a sunny afternoon after a long day of sightseeing.

Another very positive aspect of De Ceuvel is that there are mainly locals (or at least it seems like that).

Definitely a nice spot to get an impression of the ‘non-touristic’ Amsterdam!

Review:
Café de Ceuvel is a restaurant on a mission: the menu carefully articulates there is a wider vision to deliver an eco-friendly and low environmental impact. There is a rough and ready feel; a reflection on the increasing trend towards sustainability and authenticity at the expense perhaps of luxury and, perhaps, the basic proposition.
So with very high praise and reviews, we came here for lunch.
Both the inside and outside decor give the feeling of an American style summer camp assembled by a shipwrecked crew with nothing to make shelter with other than washes ashore in the island with its mismatched tables and seating, home-made decorations and deliberately contrasting use of panel colour.
If a small group of dreadlocked hippies revealed themselves slouched onto patchwork beanbags wielding archaic musical instruments and lamenting the tax dodging and well-heeled patriarchy: I would have asked them where I could purchase the nearest fair trade, organically grown cold brew.
So we find ourselves at a school desk ordering from a concise lunch menu during a semi busy Saturday service. Oh, and it’s vegan bang in trend with most restaurants I went to in two weeks of grazing around Amsterdam.
Much like the decor, the food was a bit cobbled together and didn’t make much sense. Our oyster mushroom croquette with mustard greens over sourdough (it’s an open face sandwich) was less croquette and more suppli sized mushroom flavoured dough with a crust. It is a ‘croquette’ in the style of the local Dutch bitternballen which would work if it was the same size - the texture would make the dish better but not take it over the line. The open face sandwich proposition is pointless. This dish would be better conceptualised as a starter oyster mushroom bittenballen with a dip.
The cheesy padron pepper toastie is gooey and cheesy but doesn’t rise above the level of a home comfort sandwich regardless of the padron peppers.
Vegan food is a hard sell for many people and there are restaurants that are fighting to change paradigms and perceptions about vegan food making it exciting, winning hearts and minds.
This is not that place. There’s a lot here with a good location and the shabby chic is on trend but the core proposition of paying for food for enjoyment collapses.

Review:
Bien caché au fond d’une impasse au milieu d’une zone artisanale. Ancien chantier naval abandonné, l’endroit a été reconverti en lieu de vie et d’activités. Un groupe de passionnés a conclu un marché avec la municipalité qui en échange d’un bail de 30 ans leur confie le lieu à condition de le restituer complètement dépollué au terme du bail.
Tout ici a été construit, assemblé, imaginé à partir de matériaux de récupération.
Le bar, foisonnant de vie tant à l’intérieur que dehors, les bords de l’eau, avec pontons et terrasses flottantes. Partout, d’anciens  house-boats réformés et récupérés ont été posés sur le sol pollué et on circule entre eux sur les passerelles surélevées afin de laisser la place à des plantes soigneusement sélectionnées qui patiemment assurent le travail de dépollution. De multiples entreprises ont colonisé ces espaces, toutes investies dans les domaines des arts ou des sciences liées à l’écologie.
Encore un de ces lieux inclassables ou l’on peut se retrouver hors des sentiers battus, entre amis et/ou inconnus, autour d’un feu de bois au bord de l’eau au son d’une  guitare ou de bongos improvisés ou lors d’un  concours  de poésie ou de slam....
Il se passe toujours quelque chose au Café de Ceuvel.
Translated_Review:
Tucked away at the end of a cul-de-sac in the middle of a commercial zone. Formerly an abandoned shipyard, the site has been converted into a place to live and work. A group of enthusiasts struck a deal with the municipality, which in exchange for a 30-year lease entrusted them with the site, on condition that they return it completely cleaned up at the end of the lease.
Everything here has been built, assembled and imagined from recycled materials.
The bar, teeming with life both inside and out, the waterfront, with pontoons and floating terraces. Everywhere, refurbished and salvaged old houseboats have been placed on the polluted ground, and we move between them on raised walkways to make way for carefully selected plants that patiently carry out the work of decontamination. A host of companies have colonized these spaces, all involved in the arts or sciences related to ecology.
Another unclassifiable place where you can meet off the beaten track, with friends and/or strangers, around a log fire by the water, to the sound of a guitar or improvised bongos, or during a poetry or slam contest....
There's always something going on at Café de Ceuvel.
Cleaned_Review: tucked away at the end of a cul-de-sac in the middle of a commercial zone. formerly an abandoned shipyard, the site has been converted into a place to live and work. a group of enthusiasts struck a deal with the municipality, which in exchange for a 30-year lease entrusted them with the site, on condition that they return it completely cleaned up at the end of the lease. everything here has been built, assembled and imagined from recycled materials. the bar, teeming with life both inside and out, the waterfront, with pontoons and floating terraces. everywhere, refurbished and salvaged old houseboats have been placed on the polluted ground, and we move between them on raised walkways to make way for carefully selected plants that patiently carry out the work of decontamination. a host of companies have colonized these spaces, all involved in the arts or sciences related to ecology. another unclassifiable place where you can meet off the beaten track, with friends and/or strangers, around a log fire by the water, to the sound of a guitar or improvised bongos, or during a poetry or slam contest.... there's always something going on at café de ceuvel.
